D.2 Sensitivity

Preliminary experiments on the chemical element domain show that the system converges for a wide range of \gamma and \eta_t. Larger \gamma speeds contradiction resolution but may cause instability if too large. The conflict radius R should be set to include at least 95% of known contradictory pairs in the embedding space; the value 0.3 worked for SciBERT embeddings. Active frontier size of 1000 kept memory usage under 2 GB for up to 50,000 propositions.

